// AUDIT 2026-06-17 — MEDIUM severity (silent const-strip via
// container monomorphization)
//
// Gap: `container Box(T) { T value; }` stamped with `Box(const u32)`
// monomorphizes to `struct Box_u32 { uint32_t value; }` — the
// `const` qualifier on the type argument is dropped at substitution
// time.
//
// Companion class to BUG-738 (composite container args like Box(?T)
// / Box(*T) now rejected). Qualifier-bearing args (const T,
// volatile T) silently lose the qualifier instead of either being
// rejected or being propagated to the substituted field type.
//
// Real safety issue: silent erasure of a user-stated invariant.
// A caller that writes `Box(const u32)` expects writes to its
// `.value` field to fail; the callee mutates freely. Same shape
// of trust violation as BUG-738 for shape mismatch.
//
// Expected: parser/checker rejects `const` as a type arg (mirroring
//           BUG-738 named-type rule), OR const is propagated.
// Actual:   compiles clean, write succeeds.

container Box(T) { T value; }

void show(Box(const u32) b) {
    b.value = 99;        // SHOULD error — value is const u32
}

i32 main() {
    Box(const u32) b;
    show(b);
    return (i32)b.value;
}
